column4: U.S. safety agency seeks answers on fatal Tesla Autopilot crash
column5: WASHINGTON U.S. highway safety regulators have demanded that Tesla Motors Inc hand over detailed information about the design  operation and testing of its Autopilot technology following a May 7 fatal crash in which the system was in use.

column4: UPDATE 3-U.S. safety agency seeks answers on fatal Tesla Autopilot crash
column5: WASHINGTON  July 12 U.S. highway safety regulators have demanded that Tesla Motors Inc hand over detailed information about the design  operation and testing of its Autopilot technology following a May 7 fatal crash in which the system was in use.

column4: Tesla has no plans to disable Autopilot feature: WSJ
column5: Tesla Motors Inc Chief Executive Elon Musk said the electric car maker has no plans to disable its Autopilot feature in the wake of a fatal accident in which the driver of a Model S car was using the technology  the Wall Street Journal reported.

column4: REFILE-Tesla has no plans to disable Autopilot feature - WSJ
column5: July 12 Tesla Motors Inc Chief Executive Elon Musk said the electric car maker has no plans to disable its Autopilot feature in the wake of a fatal accident in which the driver of a Model S car was using the technology  the Wall Street Journal reported.

column4: SEC investigates Tesla for possible securities law breach: WSJ
column5: DETROIT The Securities and Exchange Commission is investigating whether Tesla Motors Inc waited too long to disclose a fatal crash in May that called into question the safety of a system in the car that takes control of steering and braking  the Wall Street Journal reported on Monday  citing an unnamed source.
